[{"question":"What would you be doing right now, if you were in that job now?","answer":"If I was in that job now, I would probably be sitting in Washington waiting for the current crisis to pass.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":31,"aSentId":32},{"question":"Or is there, as some people, a chance that this could be more serious?","answer":"I think it sounds kind of similar, piers, but I think there is something different this time.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":40,"aSentId":41},{"question":"What is the significance of that?","answer":"Well, the amazing thing about north Korea is that it takes totalitarianism to an entirely new level, and besides all the control and the repression, there\u0027s a classification system that is superimposed on the entire society.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":54,"aSentId":55},{"question":"It is really, as John was saying there, totalitarianism gone crackers, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"It is an unusual place.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":63,"aSentId":64},{"question":"I mean, what should the American administration led by, say, John Kerry in South Korea, how should they be conducting themselves directly with the North Koreans would you say?","answer":"Well, I think, right now, I would agree with what Bob said earlier.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":76,"aSentId":77},{"question":"Is that true, as far as you\u0027re aware?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":90,"aSentId":91},{"question":"How are you?","answer":"Good.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":130,"aSentId":131},{"question":"Why are you doing it and what do you hope to achieve?","answer":"It\u0027s gotten out of hand.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":154,"aSentId":155},{"question":"Do you know how much this is all going to cost you, too?","answer":"It could be from $50,000 to $100,000 a night, it looks like.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":174,"aSentId":175},{"question":"Free coffee as well?","answer":"Free coffee, as well.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":203,"aSentId":204},{"question":"-- of America right now?","answer":"I mean it\u0027s embarrassing.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":223,"aSentId":224},{"question":"What do you make of the dysfunction in Washington, where they can\u0027t seem to get any kind of budget deals done, any kind of economic plan sorted, nothing?","answer":"Oh, they\u0027re -- they\u0027re out of their frickin\u0027 minds.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":229,"aSentId":230},{"question":"Do you feel the gap between the rich and poor is just widening all the time now?","answer":"I think so.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":238,"aSentId":239},{"question":"Can\u0027t we just talk about fun stuff, girls and lakes, summertime?","answer":"We can come to girls in a moment, don\u0027t you worry.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":262,"aSentId":263},{"question":"How would you describe where you are politically now?","answer":"I\u0027m pretty confused, though.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":274,"aSentId":275},{"question":"Why did you give up on Obama?","answer":"Just the whole way things were going with -- especially just -- just separating the country even more.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":285,"aSentId":286},{"question":"But was that his fault?","answer":"Someone\u0027s got to take the blame.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":288,"aSentId":289},{"question":"On the -- on the gay rights, gay marriage thing, are you from the -- you couldn\u0027t really give a damn category?","answer":"I don\u0027t care.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":302,"aSentId":303},{"question":"It\u0027s very touchy, but I think at the end of the day, man, it\u0027s got to fall on the woman, you know?","answer":"Guns.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":323,"aSentId":324},{"question":"Are you in favor of any gun control?","answer":"The only thing I could think of that might work -- no, I\u0027m not for gun control.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":326,"aSentId":327},{"question":"Do you own a lot of guns yourself?","answer":"Yes, tons.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":342,"aSentId":343},{"question":"Would you consider yourself to be safe with them?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":344,"aSentId":345},{"question":"It\u0027s as simple as that?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":349,"aSentId":350},{"question":"So you think you need to have one for protection?","answer":"I need to have one.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":351,"aSentId":352},{"question":"And you wouldn\u0027t hesitate to use it?","answer":"No, not at all.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":354,"aSentId":355},{"question":"What if you\u0027re one of the families from Sandy Hook school?","answer":"Well, I think there\u0027s families on both sides, from what I\u0027ve read.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":369,"aSentId":370},{"question":"There\u0027s very little compromise, is there?","answer":"Yes, and people are -- get so up in arms and get so hell bent one way or the other.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":375,"aSentId":376},{"question":"-- and Romney had lost?","answer":"That was fun.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":386,"aSentId":387},{"question":"Did he -- did he have a little joke at your expense?","answer":"He was -- I\u0027ve always said this about Obama no matter what, he\u0027s cool.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":388,"aSentId":389},{"question":"What -- what did he say to you when he saw you again?","answer":"He probably said, you know, I think when I popped up in the receiving line, I was like -- he\u0027s like, Kid Rock, and I\u0027m like, hey, man --","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":394,"aSentId":395},{"question":"What goes on in that moment?","answer":"Because it came from Kid, it was expected.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":415,"aSentId":416},{"question":"A big gamble, though, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"I will say we left that night -- I\u0027ve had many of those dinners.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":425,"aSentId":426},{"question":"You got some?","answer":"That\u0027s what Willie Nelson said.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":455,"aSentId":456},{"question":"Good thing?","answer":"Legalize it, tax the hell out of it.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":458,"aSentId":459},{"question":"Simple as that?","answer":"Yeah.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":460,"aSentId":461},{"question":"How old is your boy now?","answer":"Twenty.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":474,"aSentId":475},{"question":"What did you say to him about drugs?","answer":"Careful.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":477,"aSentId":478},{"question":"Not, don\u0027t do it?","answer":"No, because remember that time I came home, fell down, I think it was Christmas Eve, slept on the bathroom floor.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":479,"aSentId":480},{"question":"You\u0027re a living warning, basically?","answer":"Kind of, yeah.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":485,"aSentId":486},{"question":"Is he a mate?","answer":"I got to have dinner with Clint and just become, you know, I\u0027d say a friend over the last few years.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":504,"aSentId":505},{"question":"What made you write it?","answer":"Well, I\u0027d wrestled with perhaps doing a book one day.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":537,"aSentId":538},{"question":"That he wouldn\u0027t have liked you talking about him?","answer":"No, not at all.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":552,"aSentId":553},{"question":"How did it come about?","answer":"Well, he had always teased me for all the years that I knew him, all the guys -- I was the youngest.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":594,"aSentId":595},{"question":"Do you know?","answer":"You know, I don\u0027t know.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":645,"aSentId":646},{"question":"But it\u0027s a fortune, right?","answer":"I would imagine to most people it\u0027s a fortune.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":656,"aSentId":657},{"question":"The great moment of your life?","answer":"Wow, that is so, so tough.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":704,"aSentId":705},{"question":"After the CNN show, lots of people call me, what can we do for you?","answer":"But it was Bruno who wanted to do more to help families living in area motels.","docId":"130412pmt","qSentId":754,"aSentId":755}]